MSI’s Intel 12th-gen laptops have been built and designed with the metaverse in mind, making them the best options on the market. But what is the metaverse, and what does it mean to be meta-ready? We unpack this below. The term metaverse is generally used to refer to the evolution of the Internet into a single virtual space that simulates real-world experiences like interacting, working, and exploring with other people – even when they are not in the same physical place. While this already exists to a degree, particularly in the gaming world, the metaverse expands upon the current experience with the improvement and prioritisation of technologies like virtual and augmented reality (VR/AR) and is powered by new and upgraded software and cloud solutions. With all of this change, it is clear that users will need to upgrade their existing hardware to support the performance requirements of the metaverse. When buying a laptop, you should therefore prioritise support for the following: <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-439480" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/MSI-metaverse.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/MSI-metaverse.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/MSI-metaverse-595x400.png 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/MSI-metaverse-300x202.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> MSI’s latest laptops are designed with the metaverse in mind and support intensive workloads across the various technologies that will define this digital shift. All of MSI’s latest laptops use the latest generation of multi-core, 12th-gen Intel Core i7 processors, as well as Nvidia RTX 30-series graphics cards – both of which benefit from impressive heat dissipation thanks to MSI’s design choices. These next-gen components work with huge RAM capacities and SSD storage to support the latest hardware like VR and AR headsets, as well as intensive software like the latest AAA video games and applications that leverage AI. These laptops also offer a lightning-fast network connection for superior connectivity to the metaverse, as well as all of the important ports – including HDMI, Thunderbolt, and USB Type-C. These metaverse-ready laptops include: Click here to learn more about MSI’s meta-ready laptops.